==English==
=== Pronunciation ===
*yoo͞'fə-mĭz"(ə)m, /ˈjuːfəˌmɪz(ə)m/, /"ju:f@%mIz(@)m/

===Etymology===
:From the Greek ''euphëmismos'', meaning the use of an [[auspicious]] word for an [[inauspicious]] one.

===Noun===
'''euphemism''' (''plural'' '''euphemisms''')

#(''[[uncountable]]'') The use of a word or phrase to replace another and that is considered less [[offensive]] or less [[vulgar]] than the word or phrase it replaces.
#(''[[countable]]'') A word or phrase that is used to replace another in this way.

